race.comment: NDOLA (1) has settled too far back at his last two starts both in stronger company. He was narrowly beaten at Caulfield this grade/trip before those. Maps for a softer run today, and with Radley's 3kg claim he looks a decent chance. Stablemate STYLISH (8) also has winning claims. Resumed this distance at Caulfield and did a big job, beaten 1L. Missed by a similar margin this grade/trip at Ballarat following. Both efforts stack right up and he jumps from a low barrier on the fresh side. HARRY'S YACHT (5) peaks on a 7-day return. Resumed with an easy win over the shorter and has threatened the two since at 1200m. Has compelling figures over today's distance, and Jamie Melham is engaged. Will go close with average luck in running. MODOWN (3) has Ethan Brown and the rails gate and will be fitter. Deserves consideration. CODIGO (9) brings strong numbers over short sprints. Tries 1400m for just the second time and is fit enough to give it a decent crack.
